WHITE RIVER &#8211; Police are having a hard time arresting or dispersing the sex workers who have made the Sabie Road near White River their place of business.Provincial SAPS spokesman, Brig Leonard Hlathi, said they need to catch them in the act in order to arrest them. The presence of sex workers on the busy road continues to cause concerns among motorists using the route. Parents travelling with their children are especially troubled by the conduct of the sex workers on the public road as they habitually expose themselves to passers-by.